         Installation instructions for pgShark

To install the pgShark module and sample scripts provided with it, just do:

  perl Build.PL
  ./Build
  ./Build install  (this step may need to be done as the superuser)

The documentation for each provided script is available using this command:

  perldoc SCRIPT_NAME

Where SCRIPT_NAME is one of the following: pgs-record, pgs-replay, pgs-sql,
pgs-debug, pgs-normalize, pgs-badger or pgs-stat.

For devel documentation, see:

  perldoc pgShark
  perldoc pgShark::protocol_2
  perldoc pgShark::protocol_3